gitCommit.subject: Add slash commands
gitCommit.body:
Add slash commands

- Introduce comprehensive e2e/page‑crud.spec.ts covering slash command menu visibility, filtering, execution, escape handling and outside clicks
- Add `data-testid="slash‑command‑menu"` to `SlashCommandMenu` for reliable test targeting
- Updated `slashCommandPlugin` to intercept ArrowUp/Down, Enter and Tab keys and return `true` so ProseMirror doesn’t process them; the menu component now handles navigation and selection.
- Implemented a new “Task List” slash command (id `taskList`) with icon ☐, keyword handling, and execution that creates an unchecked task list item by calling `wrapInList` with `checked: false`.
- Extended `wrapInList` to accept optional `listItemAttrs` (e.g., `{checked: boolean|null}`) so task list items can be created with a checked state.
- Enhance `SlashCommandMenu`:
  * Scroll the currently selected menu item into view when the selection changes.
  * Add a `data-index` attribute to each command item to enable reliable scrolling.
- Adjusted `--c-bg-alt` in `variables.css` from #f9fafb to #e5e7eb.
- In `SlashCommandMenu.tsx` import `slashMenuKey` from the plugin and retrieve the authoritative state directly from `props.view.state` instead of the potentially stale `props.state`.
- Adjust keyboard navigation and command execution logic to use the fresh plugin state, ensuring the menu closes and commands execute correctly.
- Add a new e2e check in `e2e/page‑crud.spec.ts` to ensure the slash‑command menu does not trigger mid‑word after a line break.
- Extend `wrapInList` in `frontend/src/components/editor/slashCommands.ts` to accept optional `listItemAttrs` (e.g., for task‑list items) and to correctly position the cursor inside the newly created paragraph after list insertion.
- Adjust related logic to use `view.dispatch` when lifting nodes and to calculate the cursor position (`replaceFrom + 3`).
- Added viewport‑aware positioning to `SlashCommandMenu`: compute an adjusted top/left after render to keep the menu fully within the window, resetting on query or active state changes.
- Introduced `adjustedPosition` signal and logic to reposition the menu when it would overflow the bottom or right edge, including fallback margins.
- Added a new e2e screenshot test that creates a page with many lines, moves the cursor to the bottom, triggers the slash menu, and asserts that the menu remains fully visible and scrolls correctly through all items.
